---

> **The problem:** 100+ contracts deploy to BNB Chain every day. Most are forks, honeypots, or dead code. The next real builder — the one VCs and airdrop hunters want to find first — is buried in the noise.
>
> **The wedge:** PulseBNB indexes every deployment in real time, runs each one through an AI classifier, and surfaces the real builders. No subscription, no token, no waitlist.

## Why this matters

| Audience | Use case |
|---|---|
| **Airdrop hunters** | Catch a builder's first contract before everyone else |
| **VCs & scouts** | Filter the firehose of deployments for real signal |
| **Builders themselves** | Reputation that follows your wallet, not your X handle |
| **Security researchers** | Spot honeypot patterns as they propagate |

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐
│ BNB RPC     │───▶│ Indexer          │───▶│ SQLite       │
│ (block tip) │    │ (Python, port    │    │ contracts +  │
└─────────────┘    │  daemon via PM2) │    │ deployers    │
                   └─────┬────────────┘    └──────┬───────┘
                         │                        │
                         ▼                        ▼
        ┌────────────────────────┐    ┌────────────────────┐
        │ AI Classifier          │    │ FastAPI (port 8093)│
        │ via LiteLLM router     │    │ /feed /leaderboard │
        │ -> label + reason      │    │ /hot /builder/:a   │
        └────────────────────────┘    └─────────┬──────────┘
                                                │
                         ┌──────────────────────┴─────────┐
                         ▼                                ▼
                  ┌─────────────┐                ┌────────────────┐
                  │ Next.js UI  │                │ Watchlist.sol  │
                  │ (Vercel)    │                │ (BNB mainnet)  │
                  └─────────────┘                └────────────────┘
```

## Tech stack

| Layer | Choice | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Indexer | Python 3 + APScheduler | Production-proven on Base since April 2026 (24+ days uptime, zero crashes) |
| Data source | Etherscan V2 unified API | Single key across chains, `chainid=56` for BNB |
| AI classifier | LiteLLM router → cheap model | Local routing, no per-call API costs |
| Identity | Space ID + Farcaster | BNB-native + cross-chain reputation |
| Storage | SQLite | Fast enough for the read patterns, zero ops overhead |
| API | FastAPI on port 8093 | CORS open, ready for Vercel frontend |
| On-chain | `Watchlist.sol` on BNB mainnet | Real third-party attestation, no fee, no token |

## Local dev

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Makabeez/pulsebnb.git
cd pulsebnb
python3 -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
cp .env.example .env  # add your Etherscan API key
python indexer.py     # in one terminal
./start-api.sh        # in another
curl http://127.0.0.1:8093/stats
```

## Production deployment

PM2 with absolute paths (WSL gotcha):

```bash
pm2 start ecosystem.config.js
pm2 save
```

API gets fronted via Cloudflare tunnel on `pulsebnb-api.baserep.xyz`, frontend deployed on Vercel at `pulsebnb-web.vercel.app`.

## Hackathon

Built for **[BNB Hack: Online Edition](https://www.bnbchain.org/en/hackathons/bnb-ai-hack)**, cycle starting May 2026.
Sponsor tracks: **ASI Alliance** (agentic AI classification), **Netmind** (decentralized inference).

